    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-13T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-13T11:00:00-05:00" n="935"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d935">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00 Revolutions/334: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Burdett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-13T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 13, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. Faucett plane returned to Lima last night. Pilot reports he was fired upon
                    over Laredo, rebels holding suburb of <persName corresp="#p_TMGRL1"
                        >Trujillo</persName> July 12, 5 p.m., fighting continues, Government
                    shooting all prisoners caught with arms. Now verified that non-combatants were
                    killed and many atrocities committed by both sides.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_WN1">Whyte</persName> is safe at Salaverry but reports he
                    cannot communicate with <persName corresp="#p_TMGRL1">Trujillo</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Burdett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
